Workers at the Health Department's Civitas building in Pretoria leave work at 11am due to safety reasons. In 2018, the building was declared unsafe. The department is yet to find a replacement. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The implementation of National Health Insurance could be delayed due to an unsafe building. The Health Department's Civitas building in Pretoria was declared unsafe in 2018, and no alternative space has been found. READ: Gauteng health department faces R1.1bn in negligence claims Workers are refusing to enter. Instead, they gather in the lobby and leave by 11am every day.